    "faq_label": "FAQ",
    "faq_title": "Security questions, answered",
    "faq1_q": "Can ThePost.Space employees read my messages?",
    "faq1_a": "No — technically impossible. Your private key never leaves your device. Our servers only store ciphertext. Even with full database access, no employee can decrypt your messages.",
    "faq2_q": "What happens if I lose my private key?",
    "faq2_a": "We provide secure, encrypted key backup during setup — protected by your master password. You can also store a recovery key in an external password manager. Without a backup, past messages cannot be recovered, which is intentional.",
    "faq3_q": "Are messages encrypted when sent to non-ThePost users?",
    "faq3_a": "Messages to external email addresses are secured with TLS in transit, but cannot use end-to-end encryption as the external server controls the destination keys. We clearly label this distinction in the interface.",
    "faq4_q": "Has ThePost.Space ever received a government data request?",
    "faq4_a": "We publish a transparency report. Even if we receive a legally valid request, the only data we can provide is metadata — we have no ability to hand over message content since we don't possess the keys.",
    "faq5_q": "Where is my data physically stored?",
    "faq5_a": "EU user data is stored exclusively in ISO 27001-certified data centres within the EU (Frankfurt and Amsterdam). Users can choose their preferred region. Data is never transferred outside your chosen jurisdiction without explicit consent.",
    "faq6_q": "Can I migrate my existing emails?",
    "faq6_a": "Yes, we offer one-click migration from Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo, and any IMAP-compatible provider. Our migration tool preserves your folder structure, labels, and attachments. Business and Enterprise plans also include dedicated migration support.",
    "faq7_q": "How do I enable two-factor authentication?",
    "faq7_a": "Go to Settings → Security → Two-Factor Authentication. You can choose between TOTP (authenticator app), SMS, or hardware security keys (YubiKey). We recommend using an authenticator app or hardware key for the best security.",
    "faq8_q": "Can I use ThePost with my existing email client?",
    "faq8_a": "Yes! ThePost supports IMAP and SMTP protocols, so you can use it with Thunderbird, Apple Mail, Outlook, and other email clients. Go to Settings → Email Client Setup to get your IMAP/SMTP credentials.",
